The number of infected persons is estimated at a hundred thousand, but only seven thousand are treated, which is due to the fact that patients often do not know that they are infected.
Hepatitis is the concept of collecting for infectious liver diseases caused by various viruses.
Symptoms are often similar - liver inflammation and yellow insufficiency are common, but the pathogens and the diseases differ from one another.
Depending on the pathogens, hepatitis viruses are spread into two different types: in hepatitis A and E, the digestive tract (e.g. by contaminated foods or water), in hepatitis B, C and D, viruses can be transmitted through blood and other body fluids (e.g. sperm, secret or speak).
Travellers are advised to vaccine against viruses A and B, in any case, against the virus C there is no vaccine.
